lead_paragraph: Thirty-year-old Ana is an ambulance driver. While good at her job, she has problems relating in her personal life. Unbeknownst to her, she suffers from a Borderline Personality Disorder. The circumstances and stresses around her push her to outbreaks of self-destructive behavior and alcohol abuse. Ana is incapable of getting what she wants most: happiness.
